 </em>Health and Social Care Information Centre</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><em>Notes: </em></p><p> </p><ol start="1" type="1"><li>Figures are presented for the Mersey Area Team and the Cheshire, Warrington &amp; Wirral Area Team covering the following CCGs:</li></ol><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Mersey Area Team</p><p> </p><p>01F NHS Halton CCG</p><p> </p><p>01J NHS Knowsley CCG</p><p> </p><p>01T NHS South Sefton CCG</p><p> </p><p>01V NHS Southport and Formby CCG</p><p> </p><p>01X NHS St Helens CCG</p><p> </p><p>99A NHS Liverpool CCG</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Cheshire, Warrington and Wirral Area Team</p><p> </p><p>01C NHS Eastern Cheshire CCG</p><p> </p><p>01R NHS South Cheshire CCG</p><p> </p><p>02D NHS Vale Royal CCG</p><p> </p><p>02E NHS Warrington CCG</p><p> </p><p>02F NHS West Cheshire CCG</p><p> </p><p>12F NHS Wirral CCG</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>When summed together the two sets of Area Team figures comprise the “Merseyside” area.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-11-04T17:29:00.772712Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101424/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101424/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101424/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","General Practitioners: Merseyside","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many GP practices have (a) opened and (b) closed in (i) Merseyside and (ii) Knowsley in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sir George Howarth","Knowsley","Mr George Howarth","212316"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101425","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>NHS England is now responsible for the funding of general practice premises refurbishment and replacement in accordance with the National Health Services (General Medical Services - Premises Cost) Directions 2013.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>NHS England will soon be publishing Principles of Best Practice that set out how area teams should review and prioritise bids for development, enabling funding to be made available where necessary.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-11-04T17:03:01.8191484Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101425/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101425/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101425/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","GP Surgeries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department has taken to ensure that funding for the refurbishment and replacement of GP premises is made available.","false","Biography information for Sir George Howarth","Knowsley","Mr George Howarth","212317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101426","Department of Health","false","2014-11-03","<p>The work announced in the Five Year Forward View relating to:</p><p> </p><p>- piloting the introduction of Multispecialty Community Providers and such providers taking over the running of their local hospital;</p><p> </p><p>- piloting the pooling of health and social care budgets between the National Health Service and the local authority delegated to Multispecialty Community Providers;</p><p> </p><p>- piloting the introduction of Primary and Acute Care Services; and</p><p> </p><p>- the process is that will ensure that Foundation Trusts are able to open general practitioner surgeries with registered lists</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>is now being developed by NHS England, Monitor, the Trust Development Authority, the Care Quality Commission, Public Health England and Health Education England. Sector involvement will be essential to this future work and more details about how they will be taking this work forward, and who they will be engaging, will be announced by them in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Monitor and NHS England share responsibility for the payment system. As set out in the Five Year Forward View, NHS England and Monitor have committed to working together to consider whether any adjustments are needed to the NHS payment regime to reflect the costs of delivering safe and efficient services for smaller providers relative to larger ones.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","212366 ; 212367 ; 212368 ; 212369","2014-11-03T17:50:05.0719659Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101426/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101426/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101426/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","NHS: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to his Answer of 23 October 2014 to the Urgent Question on Five Year Forward View, Official Report, column 1044, if he will ensure that Hartlepool constituency is a pilot area for (a) the introduction of Multispecialty Community Providers and (b) such a provider taking over the running of the local hospital.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","212365"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101427","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>This is a matter for the National Health Service locally.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We have written to Paul Garvin, Chair of the North Tees and Hartlepool NHS Foundation Trust, informing him of the hon. Member’s enquiry. He will reply shortly and a copy of the letter will be placed in the Library.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-11-04T16:42:37.0462986Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101427/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101427/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101427/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Hospitals: Stockton on Tees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the cost has been of the application for a new hospital at Wynyard by the North Tees and Hartlepool NHS Foundation Trust; and whether the costs will be reimbursed into the local health economy via the clinical commissioning group.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","212322"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101428","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>I refer the hon. Member to my answer of 15 October 2014 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=209582" target="_blank">209582</a></p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2014-11-04T17:15:00.968714Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101428/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101428/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101428/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Pancreatic Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will assess the effect of the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence's three month end of life threshold on the appraisal of treatments for advanced pancreatic cancer.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","212326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101429","Department of Health","false","2014-11-03","<p>The work announced in the Five Year Forward View relating to:</p><p> </p><p>- piloting the introduction of Multispecialty Community Providers and such providers taking over the running of their local hospital;</p><p> </p><p>- piloting the pooling of health and social care budgets between the National Health Service and the local authority delegated to Multispecialty Community Providers;</p><p> </p><p>- piloting the introduction of Primary and Acute Care Services; and</p><p> </p><p>- the process is that will ensure that Foundation Trusts are able to open general practitioner surgeries with registered lists</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>is now being developed by NHS England, Monitor, the Trust Development Authority, the Care Quality Commission, Public Health England and Health Education England. Sector involvement will be essential to this future work and more details about how they will be taking this work forward, and who they will be engaging, will be announced by them in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Monitor and NHS England share responsibility for the payment system. As set out in the Five Year Forward View, NHS England and Monitor have committed to working together to consider whether any adjustments are needed to the NHS payment regime to reflect the costs of delivering safe and efficient services for smaller providers relative to larger ones.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","212365 ; 212366 ; 212367 ; 212369","2014-11-03T17:50:05.9079499Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101429/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101429/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101429/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","General Practitioners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to his Answer of 23 October 2014 to the Urgent Question on Five Year Forward View, Official Report, column 1044, what the process is that will ensure that the local NHS Foundation Trust is able to open GP surgeries with registered lists.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","212368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101430","Department of Health","false","2014-11-03","<p>The work announced in the Five Year Forward View relating to:</p><p> </p><p>- piloting the introduction of Multispecialty Community Providers and such providers taking over the running of their local hospital;</p><p> </p><p>- piloting the pooling of health and social care budgets between the National Health Service and the local authority delegated to Multispecialty Community Providers;</p><p> </p><p>- piloting the introduction of Primary and Acute Care Services; and</p><p> </p><p>- the process is that will ensure that Foundation Trusts are able to open general practitioner surgeries with registered lists</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>is now being developed by NHS England, Monitor, the Trust Development Authority, the Care Quality Commission, Public Health England and Health Education England. Sector involvement will be essential to this future work and more details about how they will be taking this work forward, and who they will be engaging, will be announced by them in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Monitor and NHS England share responsibility for the payment system. As set out in the Five Year Forward View, NHS England and Monitor have committed to working together to consider whether any adjustments are needed to the NHS payment regime to reflect the costs of delivering safe and efficient services for smaller providers relative to larger ones.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","212365 ; 212366 ; 212368 ; 212369","2014-11-03T17:50:05.6579545Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101430/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101430/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101430/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","NHS: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State 