"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101431","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>We have made no such assessment. The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence is an independent body and is responsible for the development of its methods and processes, which it periodically updates in consultation with stakeholders.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2014-11-04T17:22:16.3189182Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101431/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101431/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101431/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Pancreatic Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will make an assessment of the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence's technology appraisal criteria in relation to the provision of new treatments for patients with pancreatic cancer.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","212359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101432","Department of Health","false","2014-11-03","<p>The work announced in the Five Year Forward View relating to:</p><p> </p><p>- piloting the introduction of Multispecialty Community Providers and such providers taking over the running of their local hospital;</p><p> </p><p>- piloting the pooling of health and social care budgets between the National Health Service and the local authority delegated to Multispecialty Community Providers;</p><p> </p><p>- piloting the introduction of Primary and Acute Care Services; and</p><p> </p><p>- the process is that will ensure that Foundation Trusts are able to open general practitioner surgeries with registered lists</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>is now being developed by NHS England, Monitor, the Trust Development Authority, the Care Quality Commission, Public Health England and Health Education England. Sector involvement will be essential to this future work and more details about how they will be taking this work forward, and who they will be engaging, will be announced by them in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Monitor and NHS England share responsibility for the payment system. As set out in the Five Year Forward View, NHS England and Monitor have committed to working together to consider whether any adjustments are needed to the NHS payment regime to reflect the costs of delivering safe and efficient services for smaller providers relative to larger ones.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","212365 ; 212367 ; 212368 ; 212369","2014-11-03T17:50:05.562058Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101432/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101432/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101432/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","NHS: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to his Answer of 23 October 2014 to the Urgent Question on Five Year Forward View, Official Report, column 1044, if he will ensure that Hartlepool constituency is a pilot area for the pooling of health and social care budgets between the NHS and the local authority delegated to Multispecialty Community Providers.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","212366"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101433","Department of Health","false","2014-11-03","<p>The Department has not issued specific guidance where patients who have been engaged in prostitution have been referred by the National Health Service for counselling or therapeutic services.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence has issued guidelines for access to therapeutic services.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-11-03T16:31:36.0155795Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101433/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101433/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101433/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Mental Health Services: Prostitution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what guidance his Department issues on minimum standards of care in situations where patients who have been engaged in prostitution have been referred by the NHS for counselling or therapeutic services.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","212221"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101434","Department of Health","false","2014-11-03","<p>This is a matter for NHS England which is currently undertaking a review of congenital heart services for the whole pathway of care which includes paediatric cardiac surgical services, and the extent of provision of those services.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>NHS England will provide appropriate funding for services as they are commissioned.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-11-03T17:54:00.1113948Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101434/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101434/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101434/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Heart Diseases: Gloucestershire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether he plans to provide (a) further funding for and (b) expanded provision of paediatric cardiac surgery services in Gloucestershire; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","212240"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101435","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>I refer my Rt. hon. Friend to the answer I gave to my Rt. hon Friend, the Member for Sutton Coldfield (Mr Andrew Mitchell) on 27 October 2014 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=211129" target="_blank">211129</a>.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-11-04T17:08:01.0485353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101435/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101435/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101435/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Medical Equipment: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will take steps to ensure the routine commissioning of cough assist machines in the West Midlands; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dame Caroline Spelman","Meriden","Mrs Caroline Spelman","212192"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101436","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>I refer my Rt. hon. Friend to my answer of 17 October 2014 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=209881" target="_blank">209881</a>.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2014-11-04T17:20:18.456966Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101436/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101436/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101436/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Prostate Cancer: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 14 October 2014 to Question 209881, when he expects to announce a decision on allowing an application for a second Patient Access scheme for Zytiga (abiraterone); and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Paul Burstow","Sutton and Cheam","Paul Burstow","212193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101437","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>In order for codes relating to new treatment functions to flow to the Secondary Uses Service, the national repository for secondary care data, a revision to Commissioning Data Sets is required. The last revision was in September 2012 and at present there are no plans for a subsequent version in the near future.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-11-04T17:27:52.3642876Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101437/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101437/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101437/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Out-patients","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when the Health and Social Care Information Centre next plans to review the list of treatment function codes for outpatient procedures.","false","Biography information for Paul Burstow","Sutton and Cheam","Paul Burstow","212194"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101438","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>Paediatric continence has not been submitted for consideration as a new treatment function.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The guidelines for proposal and acceptance of new Treatment Functions can be found at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>http://www.isb.nhs.uk/documents/isb-0028/amd-17-2012/index_html</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Of particular relevance is the document that relates to acceptance criteria for a new Treatment Function.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Proposals for new Treatment Functions can be logged by contacting the Health and Social Care Information Centre Enquiries on <a href="mailto:enquiries@hscic.gov.uk" target="_blank">enquiries@hscic.gov.uk</a></p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-11-04T17:34:35.9229879Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101438/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101438/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101438/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Incontinence: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent discussions he has had with the Health and Social Care Information Centre on the inclusion of a specific treatment function code for paediatric continence.","false","Biography information for Paul Burstow","Sutton and Cheam","Paul Burstow","212195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101439","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>The information is not collected centrally, therefore no assessment has been made.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Audit Commission published a report in April 2012, <em>By definition - Improving data definitions and their use by the NHS. </em>The report identified that the decision as to whether activity should be recorded (and paid) as an inpatient or outpatient is often down to local discretion, yet its impact on finances can be considerable.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-11-04T17:04:31.3943022Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101439/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101439/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101439/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Out-patients","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the potential financial effect of NHS healthcare trusts failing to properly record data on outpatient procedures.","false","Biography information for Paul Burstow","Sutton and Cheam","Paul Burstow","212196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101440","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>In 2012-13, Hospital Episode Statistics for England recorded 13,037 admissions with a primary diagnosis of constipation, for patients aged 18 years or under. Admissions do not represent the number of patients, as a person may have more than one admission within the period.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We are advised that NHS England does not collect information centrally on the cost of treating these admissions.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence published a quality standard on constipation in children and young people in May 2014 which can be found at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>www.nice.org.uk/guidance/qs62/informationforpublic</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-11-04T17:32:52.4836846Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101440/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101440/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Constipation: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many hospital admissions there were for constipation in children in 2013; and what the estimated cost to the NHS was of treating such admissions.","false","Biography information for Paul Burstow","Sutton and Cheam","Paul Burstow","212197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101441","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>We are informed by NHS England that it will only consider those medicines that it is responsible for through its directly commissioned services, primarily specialised commissioning.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Where the National institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) is unlikely to appraise a medicine, the specialised services clinical reference group will be asked to review the evidence for the medicine in question and draft a clinical commissioning policy.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Those medicines that fall outside NHS England’s direct commissioning responsibility will need to be considered by individual clinical commissioning groups.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Medicines that are not recommended by NICE are generally not considered by NHS England for routine commissioning.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2014-11-04T17:09:12.527285Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101441/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101441/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Prescription Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether medicines which do not meet the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence's (NICE) Technology Appraisal and Highly Specialised Technologies prioritisation criteria or fall outside NICE's remit are automatically referred to NHS England for an appraisal.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","212249"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101442","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>We are informed by NHS England that the only criteria required are that the medicine falls within NHS England’s responsibility for directly commissioned services and that the medicine will not be reviewed through the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence’s (NICE) technology appraisal and highly specialised technologies programmes.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Under certain circumstances, for example, where there is a clinical urgency to provide access to a particular medicine prior to receiving final guidance from NICE, NHS England may adopt an interim policy.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Draft policies produced by the relevant clinical reference group are endorsed by the Clinical Priorities Advisory Group and then confirmed by the Specialised Commissioning Oversight Group.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2014-11-04T16:58:13.7283249Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101442/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101442/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Prescription Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what criteria a newly licensed medicine must fulfil in order to be considered for an interim clinical commissioning policy by NHS England; and what the process is for establishing such a policy by NHS England.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","212248"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101443","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>The information is not held centrally. The National Down Syndrome Cytogenetic Register (NDSCR) estimates that in 2012, 775 babies were born with Down’s syndrome in England and Wales. The NHS Fetal Anomaly Screening Programme reports that there are approximately 60,000 people with the condition currently living in the United Kingdom.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The NDSCR was established in 1989 and collects all cytogenetic or DNA reports of trisomies 21, 18 and 13 and their cytogenetic variants occurring in England and Wales. These data are used to (1) monitor the Down syndrome antenatal screening and diagnostic services (2) provide data on annual numbers of affected births to help those planning for their health, educational and social care and (3) provide information for research into Down, Edwards and Patau syndromes. Further information is available from the NDCSR annual reports that appear on the Wolfson Institute of Preventative Medicine Queen Mary University of London website:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.wolfson.qmul.ac.uk/current-projects/downs-syndrome-register" target="_blank">http://www.wolfson.qmul.ac.uk/current-projects/downs-syndrome-register</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-11-04T16:55:39.3489247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101443/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101443/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101443/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Down's Syndrome","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people with Down’s syndrome there were in the UK aged (a) under 15, (b) 15 to 30, (c) 30 to 50 and (d) over 50 on the latest date for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","212275"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101444","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>The Government expects that caesarean sections are managed in accordance with the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence Guideline CG132, “Caesarean Section”, published in November 2011. This guideline does not seek to define acceptable caesarean rates. Rather it recommends that if a woman requests a caesarean section without clinical indication, a discussion about the risks and benefits of caesarean section compared with vaginal birth should take place with members of the maternity team, including the midwife, obstetrician and anaesthetist. This will enable all aspects of her wishes and circumstances to be taken into account and ensure the risks and benefits to the mother and baby are properly understood.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-11-04T17:23:54.3568737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101444/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101444/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101444/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Caesarean Sections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will take steps to reduce the number of births by caesarean section in the UK.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","212276"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101445","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>The Department has no plans to commission research on this topic. The Department's National Institute for Health Research welcomes funding applications for research into any aspect of human health, including potential links between births by caesarean section and the incidence of autism and ADHD. These applications are subject to peer review and judged in open competition, with awards being made on the basis of the importance of the topic to patients and health and care services, value for money and scientific quality.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2014-11-04T16:46:10.5066812Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101445/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101445/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101445/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Caesarean Sections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will commission research to investigate the potential link between births by caesarean section and the incidence of autism and ADHD.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","212272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101446","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>Safe staffing numbers are published on NHS Choices – for the first time in the NHS’ history under this government.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>NHS Choices is a Department of Health funded programme, commissioned by NHS England and delivered by the Health and Social Care Information Centre. As part of this funding, NHS England commissioned NHS Choices to create a patient safety hub and publish safety-related data, including safe staffing numbers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>A core facility of NHS Choices includes hospital profiles which are editable and managed by hospitals themselves. NHS hospitals have been publishing staffing information on their profiles since June 2014.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-11-04T16:50:54.2602919Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101446/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101446/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101446/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","NHS: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what funding his Department is providing to assist NHS hospitals in implementing the systems and processes required to efficiently capture, manage and publish safe staffing numbers.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","212188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101447","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>The Department has not commissioned any research on the effect that publishing safe staffing data has on patient choice.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Sir Robert Francis QC’s report into the failings at Mid Staffordshire NHS Foundation Trust recommendations led to fundamental changes in the health and care system supporting a culture of transparency and openness. The Inquiry showed that transparency is an important driver of more efficient, higher-quality services. It empowers patients by making available information to patients and the public and improves outcomes for all.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>NHS Choices has introduced My NHS which incorporates patient safety indicators. The data on My NHS includes mandatory reporting of monthly actual and planned staffing levels by hospital wards.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-11-04T17:25:48.9977014Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101447/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101447/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101447/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","NHS: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what research his Department has commissioned on the effect that publishing safe staffing data has on patient choice.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","212189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101448","Department of Health","false","2014-11-03","<p>This information is not held centrally. The occupation of people using Improving Access to Psychological Therapy services is not collected or reported.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-11-03T16:30:25.8501348Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101448/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101448/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101448/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Mental Health Services: Prostitution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many patients who have been engaged in prostitution were referred by the NHS for counselling or therapeutic services in each year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","212223"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101449","Department of Health","false","2014-11-04","<p>The Department is seeking to commission a strategic initiative of research to evaluate the Government’s response to the Francis report and help inform future policy. It is planned that the initiative will initially comprise six projects, including a project on safe staffing levels. The specification document for the call for research proposals is available on the Policy Research Programme Central Commissioning Facility website at the following address:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.prp-ccf.org.uk/PRPFiles/Evaluation%20of%20response%20to%20Francis%20Inquiry%20-%20ITT%20v1.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.prp-ccf.org.uk/PRPFiles/Evaluation%20of%20response%20to%20Francis%20Inquiry%20-%20ITT%20v1.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>However, data in relation to safe staffing numbers is currently published on NHS Choices (www.nhs.uk).</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-11-04T16:53:47.2970469Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101449/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101449/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-28","Nurses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what research his Department has commissioned on the potential benefits of real-time reporting of nurse staffing numbers at NHS hospitals.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","212184"
