"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101065","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-11-03","<p>My Department has been working with the Ministry of Justice, who in turn have been working with the Information Commissioner, on changes to the rules about local authority members' notifying the Information Commissioner's Office that they are data controllers, to ensure that any new rules both remove bureaucratic burdens whilst ensuring that local authority members who are data controllers remain aware of their duties and obligations as data controllers.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-11-03T16:54:27.3454567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101065/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101065/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101065/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-10-27","Local Government: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to his Depatment's press release of 3 July 2013, entitled Government removes volunteering tax on councillors, what progress his Department has made in implementing the proposal set out in that press release.","false","Biography information for Mike Gapes","Ilford South","Mike Gapes","212132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101066","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-11-03","<p>MyDeposits is audited by FSPG Chartered Accountants and their company accounts are available online at Companies House. (http://www.companieshouse.gov.uk/index.shtml)<br><br>The scheme administrator Hamilton Fraser Insurance Plc is also regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-11-03T17:24:52.6726227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101066/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101066/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101066/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-10-27","Tenancy Deposit Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, who audits My Deposits; and whether that audit is submitted to his Department.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","212088"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101067","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-11-03","<p>All three tenancy deposit schemes are required to submit monthly key performance indicators to the Department for Communities and Local Government in accordance with the Service Concession Agreement. The schemes are also required to provide the Department with annual updates of all their management and financial plans.<br><br>In addition the Department holds quarterly monitoring meetings with the schemes at which any performance issues can be discussed. Over the period that the schemes have been in operation their performance has been consistently high.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","212086 ; 212089","2014-11-03T17:18:19.7837027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101067/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101067/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101067/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-10-27","Tenancy Deposit Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, who is responsible for checking and monitoring (a) the Deposit Protection Service, (b) the Tenancy Deposit Scheme and (c) My Deposits.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","212087"
