"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101158","Department of Health","false","2014-10-30","<p>People are ordinarily told to seek advice, provided that they are not suffering from a severe acute illness requiring immediate emergency care, by calling their Public Health England monitoring officer (if they are in the returning worker monitoring programme) or calling NHS 111. They may advise attendance at an Emergency Department for assessment (in such circumstance the Emergency Department concerned would have been pre-warned of the arrival of the patient to ensure that appropriate infection control measures are in place).</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-10-30T17:06:44.7779441Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101158/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101158/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101158/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-10-27","Ebola","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what guidance his Department has issued on whether people displaying symptoms associated with the Ebola virus should attend accident and emergency departments.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","212113"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101159","Department of Health","false","2014-11-03","<p>A modernised Nursery Milk Scheme is currently under development and expected to be tendered in due course. The aim of the scheme remains to supply nursery milk to all eligible settings.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government’s response to the consultation document <em>Next Steps for Nursery Milk </em>was published on 27 March earlier this year setting out the preferred option for modernising the scheme. The Impact Assessment, also published on 27 March sets out the impact of the preferred option, including any impact on the supply of milk. These documents are attached and also available at the following web links:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/making-the-nursery-milk-scheme-more-cost-effective</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukia/2014/110</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>It is the Department’s intention to ensure that a modernised Nursery Milk Scheme includes opportunities for small and medium-sized enterprises, and farmers, to be fully involved with the scheme.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-11-03T17:15:31.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101159/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101159/answer","Nursery_Milk_Gov Response 27 March 2014.pdf ; Next Steps for Nursery_Milk_consultation_document 2012.pdf ; Updated Nursery Milk  Impact Assessment 2014  ukia_20140110_en.pdf","Nursery_Milk_Gov Response 27 March 2014.pdf ; Next Steps for Nursery_Milk_consultation_document 2012.pdf ; Updated Nursery Milk  Impact Assessment 2014  ukia_20140110_en.pdf","Nursery Milk Government Response ; Nursery Milk Consultation ; Nursery Milk Impact Assessment","Nursery Milk Government Response ; Nursery Milk Consultation ; Nursery Milk Impact Assessment","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/101159/answer",,,,,"17","Healt